SEVEN thugs were killed in the early hours of this morning in Isipingo area, south of Durban. KZN police spokewoman, Captain Nqobile Gwala said police acted on an interlligence driven information around 01.50am. She said the information warned them about a planned robbery in one of the business premises in Isipingo area. "The suspects intended to bomb the business safes but the police placed themselves on duty and the suspects arrived. As soon as they saw that there were police in the vicinity, they opened fire towards the police," said Gwala. She said gunfire ensued as the police also exchanged gunfire. "A total of seven suspects died at the crime scene while one was arrested," said Gwala. She said the crime scene is still active.